/*! \mainpage Isogemetric Finite Element Elasticity applications

\author Knut Morten Okstad, SINTEF Digital, Trondheim

\section intro Introduction
This is a set of elasticity applications built on top of the IFEM library.
The following applications can be built built:

\li **LinEl** is a solver for the static linear elasticity equation
over 2D or 3D continuum domains, as well as for some beam, plate
and shell formulations. The application can also perform eigenvalue analysis
(free vibration and linearized buckling), and perform adaptive analysis,
based on either the exact error distributions (for problems with known
analytical solution) or recovery-based error estimates.

\li **ShellEl** is a solver for quasi-static nonlinear shell analysis based
on Kirchhoff--Love shell formulation. The application can also solve
snap-through problems using arc-length path-following solution algorithms.

\li **NonLinEl** is a solver for quasi-static and dynamic finite deformation
problems over 2D or 3D continuum domains. Hyper-elastic and elasto-plastic
material behavior is supported, in addition to linear elastic materials.

Refer to the documents in the sub-folder <i>doc/Integrands</i>
for the underlying equations forming the basis of the integrand implementations.

IFEM is an object-oriented toolbox for implementing isogeometric finite element
(FE) solvers for linear and nonlinear partial differential equations (PDEs).
The toolbox is developed through the ICADA project at SINTEF Digital, Trondheim.
The purpose of this code is to serve as a common base for isogeometric
PDE-simulators, using splines and NURBS as basis functions in the FE
formulations. The toolbox contains methods for doing linear and nonlinear,
stationary and dynamic time-domain analyses, as well as eigenvalue analyses.
*/
